Rules of JSX 

JSX isn't real HTMl
It's a Javascript in disguise 
Every component must return a single root element 
They need to be wrapped in a parent container 


Returning from functions 

1.You can't return two or more objects from a function without wrapping into an array .
2.You can't retunr two or more JSX elements without wrapping them into a parent element .

3.Every component must return a single root element 


Rule #3

- Attribute name must be written in camelCase
- Jsx is extension of javascript , html attributes that conflic with javascript keywords need different names 
- since attributes written in JSX become keys of javascript objects they need to be valid javascript variabe names 

Rule #4
You can embed Javascript expression directly in your markup using curly braces 

